TITLE: Accessing Modal State with useAppKitState (Ethers) TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates using the useAppKitState hook from `@reown/appkit-ethers-react-native` to access the current reactive state of the modal. It shows destructuring the `open` (boolean indicating modal visibility) and `selectedNetworkId` (number representing the current chain ID) properties from the hook's return value. These values update automatically as the modal state changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reown-com/reown-docs/blob/main/appkit/react-native/core/hooks.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { useAppKitState } from '@reown/appkit-ethers-react-native'

const { open, selectedNetworkId } = useAppKitState()
```

