TITLE: Fetching Specific Subscribers from Reown Notify API using JavaScript Fetch
DESCRIPTION: JavaScript example using `fetch` to query the `/v1/<project-id>/subscribers` endpoint for subscription status of specific accounts (max 100). Requires Project ID and Notify API Secret for authentication via Bearer token. Includes TypeScript type definitions for request and response bodies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reown-com/reown-docs/blob/main/appkit/next/notifications/backend-integration.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const PROJECT_ID = '<PROJECT_ID>'
const NOTIFY_API_SECRET = '<NOTIFY_API_SECRET>'
const requestBody: RequestBody = {
  accounts: [
    'eip155:1:0x9AfEaC202C837df470b5A145e0EfD6a574B21029',
    'eip155:1:0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000'
  ]
}

const response = await fetch(`https://notify.walletconnect.com/v1/${PROJECT_ID}/subscribers`, {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    Authorization: `Bearer ${NOTIFY_API_SECRET}`
  }
  body: JSON.stringify(requestBody)
})

const subscribers: ResponseBody = await response.json()

type RequestBody = {
  // Max 100 accounts
  accounts: string[]
}
type ResponseBody = {
  [account: string]: Subscriber
}
type Subscriber = {
  notification_types: string[]
}
```

