TITLE: Sending Notifications with JavaScript Fetch API
DESCRIPTION: Example of sending a notification using JavaScript's fetch API. Includes setting the project ID, API secret, and constructing the request with notification details and target accounts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reown-com/reown-docs/blob/main/appkit/react/notifications/backend-integration.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const PROJECT_ID = "<PROJECT_ID>";
const NOTIFY_API_SECRET = "<NOTIFY_API_SECRET>";
const response = await fetch(
  `https://notify.walletconnect.com/${PROJECT_ID}/notify`,
  {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      Authorization: `Bearer ${NOTIFY_API_SECRET}`,
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      notification: {
        type: "a1e53b95-18e5-4af8-9f03-9308ec87b687",
