TITLE: Implementing Deep Link Handler for Phantom Wallet (Dart)
DESCRIPTION: Shows a `DeepLinkHandler` class in Flutter that uses an `EventChannel` ('com.exampledapp/events') to listen for deep links coming from the native platform side. When a link is received (e.g., from Phantom Wallet), it calls `_appKitModal.dispatchEnvelope(link)` to pass the link data to the AppKit SDK for processing, enabling communication with wallets like Phantom that rely on deep/universal links.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reown-com/reown-docs/blob/main/appkit/flutter/core/installation.mdx#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
import 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';
import 'package:flutter/services.dart';
import 'package:reown_appkit/modal/i_appkit_modal_impl.dart';

class DeepLinkHandler {
  static const _eventChannel = EventChannel('com.exampledapp/events');
  static late IReownAppKitModal _appKitModal;

  static void init(IReownAppKitModal appKitModal) {
    if (kIsWeb) return;

    try {
      _appKitModal = appKitModal;
      _eventChannel.receiveBroadcastStream().listen(_onLink, onError: _onError);
    } catch (e) {
      debugPrint('[SampleDapp] checkInitialLink $e');
    }
  }

  static void _onLink(dynamic link) async {
    try {
      _appKitModal.dispatchEnvelope(link);
    } catch (e) {
      print(e);
    }
  }

  static void _onError(dynamic error) {
    print(error);
  }
}
```

