TITLE: Initializing Data Fetch with JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code initializes a data fetch operation from an API endpoint, handling asynchronous requests and response parsing. It requires the fetch API and handles potential errors gracefully.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reown-com/reown-docs/blob/main/appkit/vue/onboarding/wallet-features.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
async function fetchData(url) {
    try {
        const response = await fetch(url);
        if (!response.ok) {
            throw new Error('Network response was not ok');
        }
        const data = await response.json();
        return data;
    } catch (error) {
        console.error('Fetch error:', error);
        return null;
    }
}
```

